typedef struct vpsissCalCfg vpsissCalCfg_t

CAL config, used to control all the sub-modules of CAL.

struct vpsissCalCfg

Attention
Ensure to allocate before trying to configure. There is only one instance of BYSOUT, BYSIN and VPORT and hence can support only 1 channel. When these are used for multiple channels, the last config is valid
When non-CSI2 streams are being captured, following members are not applicable, stream, csi2VirtualChanNo, pixProcCfg & bysOutCfg.

typedef void(* vpsissErrorCallBack) (const UInt32 *event, UInt32 numEvents, Ptr arg)

Defines expected function type that could be called by drivers on error conditions. Please refer driver specific header files on methods to attach callbacks on errors.

Parameters
eventPointer to an array that holds event (s) that have occurred. The numEvents determine the number of elements that could accessed.
numEventsNumber of events (error conditions) that were detected.
argArgument provided while configuring the error parameters

enum vpsissCalErrorSource

Lists the possible error source in CAL reception. Applications could enable any of these and attach a function to be called on error (s) When enabled, the frame would marked with appropriate error code to indicate an issue.

Warning
If any elements are added/deleted from this structure, ensure to update VPS_ISS_CAL_MAX_ERROR_INTERRUPTS
Enumerator
VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_CMPLXIO_ERRSOTHS1 

Not supported for now !

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_CMPLXIO_FIFO_OVR 

Event triggered when CAL un able to process the received data. Typically down stream modules (including write DMA) is unable to keep up with the speed of reception of data.

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_CMPLXIO_ECC_NO_CORRECTION 

ECC module was unable to correct, as there were more than 1 bit errors. Applicable for all virtual channels

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_CMPLXIO_RSERVED_31 

Reserved event, will be used for boundary checks

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_VC_SOF1 

Not an error, Will be used for boundary checks / debug.

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_VC_CRC_MISMATCH_VC1 

CRC did not match, the frame could be BAD

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_VC_ECC_CORRECTION_VC1 

ECC module was able to correct 1 bit error

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_VC_SOF2 

Not an error, Will be used for boundary checks / debug.

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_VC_CRC_MISMATCH_VC2 

CRC did not match, the frame could be BAD

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_VC_ECC_CORRECTION_VC2 

ECC module was able to correct 1 bit error

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_VC_SOF3 

Not an error, Will be used for boundary checks / debug.

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_VC_CRC_MISMATCH_VC3 

CRC did not match, the frame could be BAD

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_VC_ECC_CORRECTION_VC3 

ECC module was able to correct 1 bit error

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_VC_SOF4 

Not an error, Will be used for boundary checks / debug.

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_VC_CRC_MISMATCH_VC4 

CRC did not match, the frame could be BAD

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_VC_ECC_CORRECTION_VC4 

ECC module was able to correct 1 bit error

VPS_CAL_CSI2_PPI_VC_RESERVED_31 

Reserved event, will be used for boundary checks

VPS_CAL_BYSIN_OVR 

When CAL is used to receive via BYS IN (Parallel input) and the down stream modules could not keep up with the incoming data rate, the BYS IN port could overflow.

VPS_CAL_CSI2_FORCE_INT 

This will ensure enum is not packed, will always be contained in int

enum vpsissCaptInstId

Different instances of capture. As name suggests, each instance is associated with a particular method of capture. Multiple instances can co-exist, provided co-existence is supported in the h/w.

struct vpsissCaptInstId

Warning
Deviation from naming convention: To enable backward compatibility
Enumerator
VPS_ISS_CAPT_CAL_A_ID 

Capture CSI2 streams via CAL. Requires to be first enum. This is requires to start with 0x0. Used an index internally in core

VPS_ISS_CAPT_CAL_A_CPI 

Capture From CPI - Via VPORT of IPIPEIF. Essentially via Parallel OR LVDS input which are interfaced to CPI port.

VPS_ISS_CAPT_CAL_A_OTF0_ID 

Capture CSI2 streams via CAL. Requires to be first enum.
